  "prompt": "I'm doing my first pyromancer build in Dark Souls 3. What stats do I need to build on to be most effective?",
  "response": "Building an effective pyromancer in Dark Souls 3 involves focusing on a few key stats to maximize your damage output and survivability. Here are the primary stats you should consider investing in:\n\n1. **Intelligence and Faith**: Pyromancies scale with both Intelligence and Faith, so you will need to raise these stats equally. Aim to get both of these stats to around 40-45 each to maximize your pyromancy damage.\n\n2. **Attunement**: This stat increases your FP (Focus Points), which are used for casting spells, and provides more attunement slots for equipping pyromancies. Investing in Attunement is crucial for a pyromancer build to ensure you have enough FP and slots to cast various spells.\n\n3. **Endurance**: Increasing Endurance will give you more stamina, allowing you to cast spells, dodge, and perform melee attacks more frequently. It's important for maintaining your mobility and ability to react in combat.\n\n4. **Vigor**: To survive longer in fights, you need a decent health pool. Investing in Vigor will increase your HP, helping you stay alive while casting spells and dealing with enemies.\n\n5. **Vitality**: While not as critical as the other stats, Vitality can be helpful for equipping better armor without becoming over-encumbered. This is less important unless you find yourself needing better protection.\n\n6. **Dexterity and Strength**: These are typically lower priorities for a pure pyromancer build, but you might want to invest a few points if you plan to wield certain weapons that complement pyromancy, or if you want to have a hybrid build with melee capabilities.\n\nAs you level up, ensure that you balance these stats according to your playstyle and the specific requirements of the pyromancies you wish to use. Additionally, acquiring and upgrading pyromancy tomes and the Pyromancy Flame will be essential for maximizing your spell damage.",
